ban Development, the authors make recommendations for future place-based siting practices, stressing its importance for ensuring more equitable urban revitalisation. The book will be a valuable resource for academic researchers and students in urban studies, housing and inequality, as well as policy makers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aHousing policyzUnited States. 0aHousingzUnited States. 0aShrinking citieszUnited States. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh1 aPatterson, Kelly L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWu, Laiyun, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aYin, Li, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311119643540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447327592423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447327592/original  a978-3-11-119643-5  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles